main event: A UFO sighting incident occurred near Seattle, Washington on September 6, 1959. It involved several objects tracked on radar and visually observed in flight for approximately 5 hours. The conclusion was that the temperature inversion and mirage effects caused the visual and radar sightings.
interesting points: Several objects were visually observed in flight and tracked on radar for approximately 5 hours.
The objects appeared to be a round, quarter-sized, with white and blue colors and a flickering light.
The flight patterns of the objects were erratic, and they usually appeared in pairs.
The observers reported a weak blip on radar and the objects fading after approximately three hours.
The sighting was associated with temperature inversion and mirage effects, causing the visual and radar sightings.
sighted object: several round, quarter-sized objects with flickering lights
witnesses: Military source and Sergeant at 13 Battery D, 2nd Missile Battalion, 43rd Artillery
